hi, P., Romano, B., A regression model for the start of the pollen season in Olea europaea (1998) Grana, 37, pp. 110-113; Galán, C., García-Mozo, H., Cariñanos, P., Alcázar, P., Domínguez-Vilches, E., The role of temperature in the onset of the Olea europaea L. Pollen season in southwestern Spain (2001) Int. J. Biometeorol., 45, pp. 8-12; Gilreath, P.R., Buchanan, D.W., Rest prediction model for low-chilling sungold nectarine (1981) J. Am. Soc. Hort. Sci., 106, pp. 426-429; Hackett, W.P., Hartmann, H.T., Inflorescence formation in olive as influenced by low temperature, photoperiod, and leaf area (1964) Bot. Gaz., 125, pp. 65-72; Hänninen, H., Modelling bud dormancy release in trees from cool and temperate regions (1990) Acta For. Fenn., 213, pp. 1-47; Janssen, P.H.M., Heuberger, P.S.C., Calibration of process-oriented models (1995) Ecol. Model., 83, pp. 55-66; Lavee, S., Datt, Z., The necessity of cross-pollination for fruit set of Manzanillo olives (1978) J. Hort. Sci., 53, pp. 261-266; Loague, K., Green, R.E., Statistical and graphical methods for evaluating solute transport models: Overview and application (1991) J. Contam. Hydrol., 7, pp. 51-73; Minero, J.G., Candau, P., Olea europaea airborn pollen in southern Spain (1997) Ann. Allergy Asthma Immunol., 78, pp. 278-284; Monteith, J.L., Climate and the efficiency of crop production in Britain (1977) Phil. Trans. R. Soc. (London), 281, pp. 277-294; Nelder, J.A., Mead, R., A simplex method for function minimization (1965) Comput. J., 7, pp. 308-313; Orlandi, F., Fornaciari, M., Romano, B., The use of phenological data to calculate chilling units in Olea europaea L. in relation to the onset of reproduction (2002) Int. J. Biometeorol., 46, pp. 2-8; Osborne, C.P., Chuine, I., Viner, D., Woodward, F.I., Olive phenology as a sensitive indicator of future climatic warming in the Mediterranean (2000) Plant Cell Environ., 23, pp. 701-710; Pinney, K., Polito, V.S., Flower initiation in Manzanillo olive (1990) Acta Hort., 2